            {{/motion}}
            {{#marginal}}




A {{widget}} is sold for \${{price}} per item.
The cost (in dollars) of manufacturing x items is given by the
following function:
C(x)={{cost_function}}



Suppose that the number of items produced is equal to the number of items sold. 
Explain how to find the marginal revenue, the marginal cost, and the marginal profit
for this situation.


            {{/marginal}}

answer.ol:
            {{#tangent}}




The equation of the tangent line is y = {{tanline}}.


            {{/tangent}}
            {{#motion}}        
                {{#elapsed}}







Position: {{position}} {{units}}






Displacement: {{displacement}} {{units}}






Velocity: {{velocity}} {{units}} per second






Speed: {{speed}} {{units}} per second






Acceleration: {{acceleration}} {{units}} per s^2




                {{/elapsed}}
            {{/motion}}
            {{#marginal}}




The marginal cost is {{marginal_cost}},
the marginal revenue is {{price}},
and the marginal profit is {{marginal_profit}}.


            {{/marginal}}
